CONSENT TO PARTICIPATE IN RESEARCH
Preferences Study

Introduction

My name is Vael Gates.  I am a graduate student at the University of California, Berkeley working with my faculty advisor, Professor Griffiths in the Department of Psychology. We are planning to conduct a research study, which I invite you to take part in.

You are being invited to participate in this study because you are a fluent English speaker, aged 18 or older and you have not participated in this experiment before. 

Purpose/Procedures

The purpose of this study is to look at people's preferences and choices. In this task, you will be asked to read stories about or watch short movies of people making choices, and answer questions related to those choices. The study will take approximately 5-10 minutes to complete. 

Benefits

Participating will provide no direct benefits to you. But, we hope that this research will benefit society at large. Many problems that people can solve very easily are very difficult to automate (to have computers solve). By revealing more about how humans learn and think, our research may help others to build and program computers that can solve these kinds of problems.

Risks/Discomforts

The risks of our study procedures do not significantly exceed the risks associated with sitting at a computer or desk and answering a series of questions. As with all online experiments, there is a risk of a breach in confidentiality, however, we will take measures to reduce the probability of a breach, and even in the case of a breach, the data collected within this study are unlikely to have a negative impact on your life should they be associated with you. 

Confidentiality

Your MTurk worker ID may be connected to individual responses, and you may be asked to provide an email address, but this will be optional (you can complete the whole study without providing an email should you choose). We will handle responses as confidentially as possible. We cannot however guarantee the confidentiality of information transmitted over the Internet. We will be keeping data collected as part of this experiment indefinitely. Identifiers might be removed from the identifiable private information. After such removal, the information could be used for future research studies or distributed to other investigators for future research studies without additional informed consent from the subject or the legally authorized representative.

Compensation

In return for your time and effort, you will be paid $1. You will receive this payment in your MTurk account within 1 week of submitting the HIT.

Rights

Participation in research is completely voluntary.  You have the right to decline to participate or to withdraw at any point in this study without penalty or loss of benefits to which you are otherwise entitled.

Questions

If you have any questions or concerns about this study, you may contact Vael Gates at vgates@berkeley.edu or Professor Griffiths at tom_griffiths@berkeley.edu.

If you have any questions or concerns about your rights and treatment as a research subject, you may contact the office of UC Berkeley's Committee for the Protection of Human Subjects, at 510-642-7461 or subjects@berkeley.edu. 

**************************************************

CONSENT

By selecting the “consent” option below, I acknowledge that I am 18 or older, that I am a fluent speaker of English, that I have not completed this experiment before, that I have read this consent form, and that I agree to take part in the research.
